灣仔新開了一間波士冰室，內裡都懷舊感覺，舊香港的鐵閘，信箱，照雞蛋紅燈罩，飲品方面很開心有黑牛（可樂+雪糕）， 雪糕紅豆冰，雜果冰，忌廉溝鮮奶，香蕉船！ 
食物方面有常餐，午餐，特別芝士撈丁，升級高級下午茶，我選了手打牛肉煎蛋漢堡伴薯條$52
份量很足，像美國一樣，完全吸睛！ 看圖！

好難食，裝修幾好以為唔錯，誰知食物水平真係好差

reviews.text: Great shopping experience with many items.

How to judge a shopping mall? 1-shop variety 2-shopping experience 3-Carpark availability 1-hard to tell because this place has a weird layout like a maze. I've been here many times and still get lost going up the different levels. 2-havent shopped here much because of 1. 3-their parking lot is often closed off. For whatever reason, they have cars waiting outside eventhough there are parking spots available. I've come to this realization after multiple times waiting for a spot. All in all this is not a place I on my rec list for visiting.
A variety of stores and eateries you find here. Two floors of parking space for those who drive.

I pretty like the place since there's Starbucks and crostini for coffee, also they have free Wi-Fi which is really good for people who wants to work or spend the day there. The mall has different restaurant as well. I highly recommend the visitors to work at crostini or Starbucks. The restroom is clean as well.
Malls in two separate sections, well arranged and maintained, wide verities of merchandise, happy to spent some time there in two days stop over
